Title : Carlos María Franzini
Text : {{more citations needed|date=December 2017}}
[[File:Coat of arms of Carlos María Franzini.svg|thumbnail|Coat of arms of Carlos María Franzini.]]
'''Carlos María Franzini''' (September 6, 1951 – December 8, 2017) was a [[prelate]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]]. He served as [[bishop]] of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Rafaela|Rafaela]] from 2000 until 2012, when he became archbishop of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Mendoza|Mendoza]].

== Life ==
Born in [[Buenos Aires]], he was [[Holy Orders|ordained]] to the [[Priesthood (Catholic Church)|priesthood]] on August 13, 1977, serving as a priest in the diocese of San Isidro.

On April 29, 2000, he was appointed [[bishop]] of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Rafaela|Rafaela]]. Polti Franzini received his [[Bishop (Catholic Church)|episcopal consecration]] on the following June 19 from [[Alcides Jorge Pedro Casaretto]], bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of San Isidro|San Isidro]], with archbishop of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Paraná|Paraná]], [[Estanislao Esteban Karlic]], and archbishop of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Mendoza|Mendoza]], [[José María Arancibia]], serving as [[Consecrator|co-consecrators]].

On November 10, 2012, he was appointed [[archbishop]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Mendoza|Mendoza]], where he was installed on February 9, 2013.

He died on December 8, 2017 at the age of 66.<ref>[https://losandes.com.ar/article/view?slug=en-el-dia-de-la-virgen-maria-murio-el-obispo-de-mendoza-carlos-maria-franzini En el Día de la Virgen María, murió el obispo de Mendoza Carlos María Franzini] {{es icon}}</ref>

